        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Best solo spot is the exit imho, for obvious reasons. I believe you have to be 57 at least to be able to 100% single pull the exit tunnel mobs. The have up to 5200 or so HPs, not particulary resistant to anything. CoS and run3/jboots/SoW will make you life a lot easier. The Chokidai Sniffers have a chance to see invis, the rest dont (sarnaks and the whelps). At 59 I usually do PE &gt; Dooming &gt; Pyro &gt; Splurt &gt; Vex. With one Dooming refresh. Replace Vex with CoC if full health.</P><P>If tunnel is full pop, I usually head invis to the middle of it, there is a safe spot there where you can med. I start my root-dot'ing from there. XP is good. Not like the Gargoyles in Katta, but good enough.</P><P>Hope this helps</P><P>&lt;img src="http://home.t-online.de/home/blueglow/images/iranicus_lotj.jpg" border=0&gt;<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=12328" target="_blank">My Gear</a><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
