			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=97')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=31860&amp;TOPIC_ID=4079&amp;FORUM_ID=3&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=Necromancer+Game+Guides&amp;Topic_Title=Chardok+Solo+tactics%3F&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I spent 20 AA points in Chardok, and it is very good experience if no one is in the zone.  </P><P>There were three areas I would solo, depending on the congestion in the zone.</P><P>Zone in/out:  There are ample mobs along this winding corridor, most of which are light blue to 60, but due to the number of them, the exp is decent.  Root, Epic Snare, Splurt, Pyro does the trick here.  They are wimpy mobs, and exp is best when you have 2-4 at a time.</P><P>Lev Tunnel:  Invis, DMF, and enter top of tunnel.  Usually an undead mob right as you enter, just root, epic snare, splurt, pyro, then add ces of cor.  This lineup works best here, and usually I would just pull one at a time.  There are several mobs with a pet.  The best method I found for these was to snare the mob, let the pet come up to you, root and epic him, then move down and root snared mob. Then apply those dots.  After getting to Captain area, there is a mob just up from the captain room on the left fork which you can take.  Then go back to Captain, and get the two mobs along the left path.  Any further down will be mobs which cannot be single pulled, and have considerably more hp's such that it was not worth the effort.  I would routinely clear to captain, med up, wait for respawn, and work my way back up.  A trip down to Captain and back up yields approximately one yellow.</P><P>Observer - Thru main gates, you can single all the mobs over the bridge and down to the observer room.  You can solo this room, but its difficult, as the observer is resistant and hits hard, and its not easy to single pull his room.  It can be done, but get some nice clerical buffs before doing it.  Once broken, this is a great place to set up and you can pull further down, or back up towards bridge.  Just keep in mind that the room has 3 mobs.</P><P>By far the Lev tunnel was my favorite, as its away from trains, and usually I was the only one there. This place is imho slightly better than HS for AA exp.  However, I have since changed faction, so I can no longer fight here.</P><P>Loots:  I received some very nice loots in this dungeon solo.  In my time there, I had 6 Sarnak Battleshields, numerous caster rings, then some lower tiered crap drops.  Also, I got 2 of the monk only staffs, both of which I sold for 12-15k.  Ironically, both dropped from the exit mob.  /em boggle.  This was awhile back, so I dont know current price on the staff.  Think it was called Staff of Shielding or something like that.  Observer drops Nasthar arms, which are common.  Also, the temple mobs dropped some decent loot.  There are two named that can spawn there, and if they were uncamped, id single pull those out. As I recall, it dropped some druid ring with effect of snare.  Again, im cloudy on the exact drops as its been so long.</P><P>Great solo dungeon, cant wait to go back once I finish my quest!</P><P>Goodluck!</P><P>Psycra<BR><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

